    "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nAdd a new `stage-b-test-small-1-gpu-5090` job to the PR test workflow for dry-running tests on RTX 5090 runners.\r\n\r\n### Key Points\r\n\r\n- **Runs in parallel** with existing stage-b tests (after stage-a)\r\n- **NOT required for PR merge** - not in `pr-test-finish` needs\r\n- **NOT blocking** - uses `continue-on-error: true`\r\n- **5 partitions** running **118 test files** registered to `stage-b-test-small-1-gpu-5090` suite\r\n\r\n### Configuration\r\n\r\n| Setting | Value |\r\n|---------|-------|\r\n| Runner | `1-gpu-5090` |\r\n| Partitions | 5 |\r\n| Suite | `stage-b-test-small-1-gpu-5090` |\r\n| IS_BLACKWELL | `1` |\r\n\r\n### Test Registration\r\n\r\nAdded `register_cuda_ci(est_time=X, suite=\"stage-b-test-small-1-gpu-5090\")` to 1 gpu test files:\r\n- Used actual elapsed times from 5090 workflow run [20954749819](https://github.com/sgl-project/sglang/actions/runs/20954749819) where available \r\n- Used existing `est_time` values for tests without 5090 data \r\n\r\n### Purpose\r\n\r\nThis allows us to monitor 5090 test stability on real PRs before fully integrating 5090 runners into the required CI pipeline. After a day of dry-running, we can evaluate results and decide on next steps.\r\n\r\n### Changes\r\n\r\n1. Added `stage-b-test-small-1-gpu-5090` job to `.github/workflows/pr-test.yml`\r\n2. Added stage to `scripts/ci/slash_command_handler.py` for `/rerun-stage` support\r\n3. Added suite to `test/run_suite.py` PER_COMMIT_SUITES\r\n4. Registered 118 test files to new `stage-b-test-small-1-gpu-5090` suite",
